"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nInstitute of Chartered Accountants in Ireland – Written evidence&#xa0;              \n              \n              \n              \n              \n              \n              \nOur Committee, on behalf of the Institute of Chartered Accountants in Ireland, confined its \nexamination\n of the provisions of this Bill to Schedule 5, Insolvency and Company Law.  Our \nspecific\n comments on those provisions are attached herewith.\n&#xa0;\nWe respond to a number of the general questions posed in the Call for Written Evidence as \nfollows\n:\n&#xa0;\nQ. 3              Are the changes proposed in the draft Bill evidence-based and have any risks associated with the changes been taken adequately into account?\n&#xa0;\nA. 3              \nWe are not convinced of the benefits/risk balance in the proposal to remove the obligation on a bankrupt to present a statement of affairs when the petition is presented by a creditor.\n&#xa0;\nQ. 4              \nDoes the draft Bill achieve its purpose of reducing the regulatory burden on business, organisations and individuals effectively and fairly?\n&#xa0;\nA. 4              \nOn balance\n, yes.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nQ. 5              \nWill the draft Bill generally benefit businesses by offsetting other regulatory burdens?\n&#xa0;\nA. 5              \nReduction in administrative burdens in insolvency assignments will reduce costs. Consequently, more funds will be available for the creditors of the insolvent business.\n&#xa0;\nQ. 6    To what extent does the draft Bill benefit consumers as well as businesses?\n&#xa0;\nA. 6    Amendments within Schedule 5 may benefit consumers who are creditors of insolvent\n           \nbusinesses\n.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nJohn Bowen-Walsh\nSecretary\nInsolvency Committee\n&#xa0;\n16\n \nSeptember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSCHEDULE 5, DRAFT DEREGULATION BILLINSOLVENCY AND COMPANY LAW&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDEEDS OF ARRANGEMENT\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nADMINISTRATION OF COMPANIES\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWINDING-UP OF COMPANIES  \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDISQUALIFICATION OF UNFIT DIRECTORS  \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nBANKRUPTCY\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nAUTHORISATION OF INSOLVENCY PRACTITIONERS\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nLIABILITIES OF ADMINISTRATIORS AND ADMINISTRATIVE RECEIVERS\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nREQUIREMENT OF COMPANY LAW\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"